== Pico de Gallo ==

Wash and dry produce. Halve, peel, and dice @red onion{1}(diced).

== Turkey and Rice ==

In a #small pot{}, combine @jasmine rice{1/2%cup}, 3/4 cup @water{}, and a 
big pinch of @salt{pinch}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce heat to 
low. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}. Keep covered off heat until 
ready to serve.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{2%tsp} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. 
Add onion and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Cook, stirring occasionally, 
until softened, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Add another drizzle of oil, @ground turkey{10%oz}, @garlic powder{1%tsp}, 
@Mexican spice blend{1%tbsp}, salt, and pepper. Cook, breaking up meat into 
pieces, until browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}.

Add @tomato paste{1.5%oz} and cook, stirring, until darkened, ~{30-60%seconds}.

Add @chicken stock concentrate{2} and 1/3 cup water; reduce heat to medium low 
and simmer until mixture is slightly thickened, ~{1-2%minutes}. Taste and 
season with salt and pepper.

> TIP: Add a splash of water if the mixture is too thick.

== Pico de Gallo ==

While turkey cooks, trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}, separating whites 
from greens; mince whites. Finely dice @tomato{1}.

In a #small bowl{}, combine scallion whites, tomato, @white wine vinegar{5%tsp}, 
and a pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{}.

== Assembly ==

Wrap @flour tortillas{6} in damp paper towels and microwave until warm and 
pliable, ~{30-60%seconds}.

Fluff rice with a fork; taste and season with salt and pepper.

Divide tortillas between plates and fill with rice and turkey. Top with pico 
de gallo and @smoky red pepper crema{4%tbsp}. Sprinkle with scallion greens and 
serve.